more me time in 2023 🤍 decided to keep this stunning @keyssoulcare Soulful Celebrations Set and I’m so glad I did. Here’s a lil first impressions:

✨ Golden Cleanser (Manuka Honey + Tumeric): this cleanser is absolutely gorgeous, look at that texture. I love how gentle yet effective it is on my combo skin. It doesn’t a great job of cleansing without drying out my skin.

✨ Skin Transformation Cream (Hyaluronic Acid) : I’m very picky about creams especially when it comes to texture, but I fell in love with the silky texture of this cream so quick. The texture is velvety and nourishing without being heavy or sitting on top of the skin. 

✨ Let Me Glow Serum (Niacinamide): I’ve been a fan of this serum for months now and I still can’t get over how much I love it. This serum smells incredible and sinks into the skin quickly, which I love for daytime serums. It also leaves a gorgeous hydrated finish on the skin and looks amazing under makeup!

in my lymphatic drainage massage era ✨ I’ve been doing at-home lymphatic massages for a few years now so I was super excited to try @thetoxtoronto 🤍 their space is so calming and relaxing! I was invited to try their Master Tox service. 

Lymphatic massage is all about relieving inflammation and water retention through the lymphatic system. This is not your typical massage and actually uses quite a bit of pressure to help move fluid to your lymph nodes. I definitely noticed a difference in my overall inflammation and digestion! I definitely think I’ll be making this a quarterly treat to maintain results!

the cold weather has been wreaking havoc on my skin, so I’m super grateful for @olay_canada Hyaluronic + Peptide24 collection! Here are my thoughts on the products:

💧Hyaluronic Acid Nourishing Body Lotion: I’m all about body lotions that sink into the skin quickly, and this texture is perfection. It’s lightweight and doesn’t leave my skin feeling coated, but it’s somehow still super hydrating and nourishing. I also love the scent! 

💧 Hyaluronic + Peptide 24 Facial Cleanser: this cleanser is super gentle and effective. I love that it’s fragrance-free, and that it’s formulated with niacinamide and HA to keep your skin hydrated. I use this as a second cleanse to remove and leftover makeup or impurities. 

💧 Hyaluronic + Peptide 24 Hydrating Serum: look at that texture!! I love using this serum in both my AM and PM routine as a quick and easy layer of hydration. Its lightweight texture and radiant finish is perfect for under makeup in the morning. 

💧 Hyaluronic + Peptide 24 Eye Gel: by the end of the day my eyes are super puffy and tired, so I love a cooling eye cream to soothe any irritation. Sometimes I even leave this in the fridge for even more of a cooling effect!

💧 Hyaluronic + Peptide 24 Gel Face Moisturizer: this is by far my favourite product from the collection for so many reasons. The lightweight and hydrating texture reminds me so much of other luxurious creams that I love, but this is way more affordable! I use this a lot in my morning routine, but when I’m skin cycling this is a must for a hydrating night routine.

hanging out with @vichylaboratoires ✨

had the best time learning all about their new Liftactiv Pure Retinol. This serum is formulated with 0.2% pure retinol, peptides, and hyaluronic acid to help reduce the look of fine lines. 

What I love most about the Pure Retinol Serum is the incredible texture. It’s so lightweight and feels amazing on the skin. This serum is also formulated with probiotic fractions to support your barrier and reduce irritation risk! 

A few tips if you plan on using a retinol: apply on dry skin to help reduce the risk of irritation, and make sure you use a good SPF! 

Thank you @vichylaboratoires and @velatoronto for an amazing night 🤍

Prepping for travel with @parissawax ✈️ I love that Parissa makes waxing at home easy and accessible with natural ingredients! Here are some of their products I love to help me prep for my upcoming vacay!

Mini Pro Wax Warmer: This wax warmer is super quick and convenient!  The silicone cup is easy to clean and I like that the warmer has different temp options depending on the type of wax you’re using.

Organic Sugar Wax: This vegan and fragrance-free wax is safe for sensitive skin and microwaveable if you don’t have your own warmer! It does a great job of painlessly removing hair.

Ingrown Rescue Kit: This travel-friendly kit helps treat any ingrowns that might pop up while on vacation! First, you cleanse with the Tea Tree soap, exfoliate with the Konjac Sponge, and nourish with the Ultra-Soothe Oil. 

Make sure to wax at least a few days before sun exposure to avoid skin damage, and don’t forget SPF!

Use Code MASK25 or the link in my bio to save 25% (no minimum purchase)
